{"word":"ἔκλυσις","slug":"ἔκλυσις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔκλυσις</b></el> <el>(ἔκλῠσις, εως) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐκλύω'><el>ἐκλύω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>release</i> or <i>deliverance from</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>feebleness, faintness</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}